The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 12: Industry grew by 8.8 per cent in February, powered by the growth in the manufacturing and electricity sectors. The index of industrial production showed that as many as 13 of the 17 industry groups had positive growth compared with the same month a year ago. During the cumulative period of April-February, IIP registered a growth of 8 per cent compared with the same period in the previous year. According to the official data released today, manufacturing sector grew by 9.5 per cent in February, electricity by 9 per cent and mining by 0.9 per cent. During April-February, manufacturing recorded a 9 per cent growth, electricity 5.3 per cent and mining 0.5 per cent growth.

 Mumbai, April 12: Siemens Ltd will conduct a postal ballot to seek shareholders? approval for the stock-split proposal, it informed stock exchanges. The company proposes to sub-divide each equity share of Rs 10 into five equity shares of Rs 2 each.

 New Delhi, April 12: The VAT panel has agreed to phase out the central sales tax (CST) in four years instead of two, reducing the burden on the government, which has to compensate states for a cut in the CST from this fiscal.

 Nagpur, April 12: A new and simplified income tax law is in the offing, which will replace the cumbersome and voluminous income tax act, said finance minister P. Chidambaram.

 New Delhi, April 12: About 1.1 million personal computers were sold during the October to December period last year, according to a survey conducted by MAIT, the apex hardware industry association.

 Mumbai, April 12: GlaxoSmithKline Biologicals, an affiliate of GSK Pharmaceuticals Ltd, today said it would aim to triple its production capacity by 2010.

 Mumbai, April 12: Himachal Futuristic Communications Ltd (HFCL) today said Mauritius-based Goldman Sachs Investments has acquired a 5.39 per cent stake in the company.




